<DOC><DOCNO> AP890222-0017 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-22-89 0039EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a AM-GunBan     02-22 0118</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Gun Ban,0121</SECOND><HEAD>Suburban Chicago Village Bans Handguns</HEAD><DATELINE>WILMETTE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Village trustees passed an ordinanceTuesday that bans the sale and possession of handguns.   Wilmette, north of Chicago, is bounded by Winnetka, where LaurieDann entered a school last May and fatally shot one child andinjured five other youngsters. Later she injured a man and killedherself.   Since that incident, gun-control activists, including PhilipAndrew, a college student who survived the ordeal, have beenadvocating a ban in many of the affluent Lake Michigan communities.   ``We're really pleased,'' said Christine Crosh, a member of agroup called the Wilmette Coalition to Ban Handguns. ``There's beentremendous community support for this.''   The vote was 7-0.</TEXT></DOC>